<task id="026" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Wire attachments[] into outbound chat-message payload (FR-07 payload wiring)</title>
    <phase>Phase B — Assistant pane</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>001, 024, 025</dependencies>
    <blocks></blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, ai, shared-components, bff-api</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Wires user-supplied content into an outbound BFF payload — directly affects AI prompt context. Auth + payload schema + telemetry surfaces all converge here. Gated by spike 001 outcome. FULL rigor mandatory.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wire the `attachments` array from `useChatFileAttachment` (task 024) into the outbound
    chat-message payload sent to `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/messages` from
    `SprkChat.tsx` (post task 025). Behavior depends on the spike 001 memo at
    `notes/spikes/001-fr07-attachments-payload.md`:
    - IF spike says current endpoint already accepts `attachments[]`: send directly in this
      task.
    - IF spike says backend schema extension needed: stage the frontend wiring against the
      planned schema, but DEFER the payload-send portion until Phase E (tasks 050/051) lands;
      record this in `current-task.md` and mark this task BLOCKED pending Phase E.
    Either way: clear attachments state after a successful send via `clearAll()`.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Full-stack engineer comfortable reading a BFF DTO contract, constructing a frontend
    payload to match, and reasoning about spike-gated branching execution paths.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SprkChat.tsx`'s send-message handler includes an `attachments: ChatAttachment[]` field
    in the outbound `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/messages` body when chips are
    present. After a successful send, `clearAll()` resets the attachment state. End-to-end
    test in Vite dev: attach 2 `.txt` files + ask "summarize" → AI reply references both
    file contents. Error path: send failure with attachments still emits the existing error
    telemetry properly, attachments are NOT cleared (user can retry).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-07's full acceptance criterion is end-to-end: user picks 5 files → backend receives
      `attachments` array of 5 → AI reply demonstrates knowledge of all 5. The hook (task
      024) and toolbar (task 025) handle the UX side; this task is the wire that connects
      them to the BFF. Spike 001 is the gatekeeper: if the endpoint already supports
      `attachments[]`, this task is straightforward. If not, Phase E (tasks 050/051) extends
      the endpoint first; this task stages the frontend wiring against the agreed schema
      so it lands cleanly when Phase E completes.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChat.tsx</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/spikes/001-fr07-attachments-payload.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Wiring lives in `SprkChat.tsx` (shared lib). Do not introduce a SpaarkeAi-specific code path — the wiring must work for all consumers of SprkChat that opt into attachments.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">AI features extend the BFF in-process. Do not introduce a new service or a parallel send path. The single outbound call is `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/messages` with attachments included.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">No styling changes in this task. Logic-only edit.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19. Use the existing send handler pattern; no parallel hooks.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">The send call uses `authenticatedFetch` (or whatever `useChatSession` / `sendMessage` already uses). MUST NOT pass `accessToken` as a parameter. Per-request token acquisition is opaque to this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-07 acceptance: AI reply demonstrates knowledge of attached file contents. NFR-04 caps (max 5, max 10 MB, allowed MIME) enforced at the hook (task 024) and reaffirmed on the backend per Phase E.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Single-LLM-call invariant (D-01 from R2 lessons): exactly ONE LLM call per user turn. `attachments[]` flow into the single chat-message body — do NOT trigger a separate extraction LLM call.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Spike 001 outcome is BLOCKING. If memo says backend extension needed, mark this task BLOCKED in TASK-INDEX (via the main session) and surface to user before proceeding past frontend staging.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
