  </execution>

  <notes>
    **Completed**: 2026-05-20

    **Spike branch**: Per spike 001 memo, the current BFF `ChatSendMessageRequest`
    DTO does NOT accept `attachments[]` today (only `Message` + `DocumentId`).
    Phase E (task 050) extends the DTO; task 051 adds BFF unit tests.

    **Strategy**: Per user instruction, send `attachments` UNCONDITIONALLY (no
    feature flag) when chips are present. System.Text.Json default behavior silently
    drops unknown properties, so the request remains valid against the current DTO
    and lands cleanly once task 050 ships. End-to-end flow works after 026 + 050
    are both merged; 051 adds BFF coverage.

    **Files modified**:
    - `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/SprkChat.tsx`
      - Renamed `_chatAttachments` → `chatAttachments` (removed `_` prefix + TODO marker)
      - Added `clearAll: clearAttachments` to the hook destructure
      - Updated `handleSend` to conditionally include `attachments: [{filename, contentType, textContent}]`
        in the POST body when `chatAttachments.length > 0`. Omitted entirely otherwise.
      - Added `clearAttachments()` call inside the `streamDone` effect so chips clear on
        successful completion. On error (`streamError`, no `streamDone`), chips remain
        for retry — error telemetry path (existing `displayError` banner at line 1948) is unchanged.
      - Added `chatAttachments` to the handleSend `useCallback` dependency list.
    - `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SprkChat/__tests__/SprkChat.attachments.test.tsx` (new)
      - Verifies: payload omits `attachments` when no chips; includes camelCase
        `attachments[]` when chips ready; calls `clearAll` on stream completion;
        no `/documents` POST triggered (OC-02 compliance).

    **Build status**:
    - `npm run build` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components` → ✅ tsc clean
    - `npm run build` in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi` → ✅ Vite build 13.03s, 3157 modules transformed

    **Test status**: New attachment payload test suite added. Cannot execute against
    the current Jest environment due to a pre-existing infrastructure issue
    (`@testing-library/react@14` requires `react-dom/client` which is React 18+ only,
    but this lib pins React 16). The EXISTING `SprkChat.test.tsx` and
    `useChatFileAttachment.test.ts` files have the same failure mode. This is NOT a
    regression introduced by task 026 — it's a pre-existing testing-environment debt
    item (out of scope for FR-07 wiring). Type-check (`tsc`) for both modified and
    new files is green via `npm run build`.

    **Acceptance criteria verification**:
    - ✅ `attachments` field included with chips present, camelCase, exact schema from spike 001
    - ✅ `clearAll()` called on stream success (via `streamDone` effect)
    - ✅ Chips preserved on error (no `clearAll` on `streamError` path)
    - ✅ Single-LLM-call invariant: one POST per send, attachments inline in same body
    - ✅ No `accessToken` props introduced — auth still via `getAccessToken` to startStream
    - ✅ Builds succeed on shared lib + SpaarkeAi
    - ⏭️ End-to-end test with mixed-MIME files: DEFERRED until task 050 lands (per FR-07
      acceptance — BFF must accept attachments[] for AI to reference content). Wiring lands
      now; end-to-end completes post-050.

    **Coordination with parallel task 050**: NO file overlap. 050 modifies `ChatEndpoints.cs`
    (DTO + handler); 026 modifies `SprkChat.tsx` (client payload). Both can land independently;
    end-to-end attachment flow works once both are merged.
  </notes>
</task>
